cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper proposes ways to improve the performance of fully connected networks, which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) since the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed methods on the CIFAR-10 dataset. The paper also discusses the use of autoencoders, which falls under the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and the reduction of sparsity in the network, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
